President Barack Obama announced that Diana Farrell and Jason Furman will serve as Deputy Directors of the National Economic Council (NEC). They will work alongside Larry Summers to advance an American Recovery and Reinvestment plan that aims to jumpstart economic growth, create jobs, rebuild infrastructure, and assure energy independence. Diana Farrell, the former Director of the McKinsey Global Institute, has experience in economics research and has worked for Goldman, Sachs & Company. Jason Furman, who took leave from the Brookings Institution, has a background in economic policy and has worked in various public service roles, including at the World Bank. Both Farrell and Furman have extensive educational backgrounds in economics and government.